HEADWORD: Cordage
<hw>Cord"age</hw> <pr>(k⟦ocir⟧rd"⟦asl⟧j)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>cordage</ets>. See <er>Cord</er>.]</ety> <def>Ropes or cords,
collectively; hence, anything made of rope or cord, as those parts of
the rigging of a ship which consist of ropes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

